column1: 1/ Chained (2012) dollar series are calculated as the product of the chain-type quantity index and the 2012 current-dollar value of the corresponding series
column2: divided by 100. Because the formula for the chain-type quantity indexes uses weights of more than one period
column3: the corresponding chained-dollar estimates are usually not additive. The difference between the United States and sum-of-states reflects federal military and civilian activity located overseas
column4: as well as the differences in source data used to estimate GDP by industry and the expenditures measure of real GDP.
